The paper discusses the design and implementation of a stateful Function-as-a-Service (FaaS) platform, which involves distributed systems, data structures, software engineering, programming languages, and control systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with cache consistency, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper presents a Python programming interface, which relates to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper mentions autoscaling benefits, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
